   But we also have `2ⁿ ≡ -1 (mod p_i)`, so `1 ≡ -1 (mod p_i)`, meaning `p_i ∣ 2`.  

   This is a contradiction because `p_i` is an odd prime.  

   **Wait, this reasoning is incorrect!**  

   Actually, `2ⁿ ≡ -1 (mod p_i)` and `2ⁿ ≡ 1 (mod p_i)` would imply `-1 ≡ 1 (mod p_i)`, i.e., `p_i ∣ 2`. But `p_i ∣ n` implies `p_i ∣ 2ⁿ + 1`, not that `2ⁿ ≡ 1 (mod p_i)`!  

