   This only holds if `p_i ∤ 2`, i.e., if `p_i` is an odd prime, but then we can use Fermat’s Little Theorem to write `2^{p_i - 1} ≡ 1 (mod p_i)`, but `n` is not necessarily divisible by `p_i - 1`.

   This line of reasoning does not seem to work directly.  

**Correct Approach:**
